text: Tyyne Järvi (4 February 1891 - 4 April 1929) was a Finnish swimmer. She competed in the women's 100 metre freestyle event at the 1912 Summer Olympics. She was the first woman to represent Finland at the Olympics. ==References== Category:1891 births Category:1929 deaths Category:Sportspeople from Vaasa Category:People from Vaasa Province (Grand Duchy of Finland) Category:Finnish female swimmers Category:Olympic swimmers of Finland Category:Swimmers at the 1912 Summer Olympics
